# ARKA Monorepo — Cursor Rules

## Scope isolation
- Do NOT modify files under app/clin/, app/ed/, components/clin/, or components/ed/ unless explicitly instructed.
- ARKA-INS work lives under app/ins/, app/api/ins/, app/api/cds-services/arka-ins-*, components/ins/, and lib/davinci/, lib/cards/.
- Shared code lives under lib/aiie/, lib/fhir/, lib/supabase/, components/shared/.

## AIIE engine
- If lib/aiie/scoring-engine.ts already exists (from ARKA-CLIN), IMPORT from it — do NOT overwrite.
- Only add INS-specific helpers as sibling files: denial-risk.ts, gold-card.ts, oop-estimator.ts.
- Never duplicate the scoring logic.

## Supabase naming
- All ARKA-INS tables are prefixed `ins_` (ins_providers, ins_pa_history, ins_gold_card_scores, ins_oop_estimates, ins_shoppable_sites, ins_validation_events).
- Never modify CLIN or ED tables.
- No PHI in any table. Patient identifiers always hashed with SHA-256.

## FDA compliance
- ARKA-INS is an FDA Non-Device Clinical Decision Support tool under Section 520(o)(1)(E) of the FD&C Act (21st Century Cures Act).
- Every CDS card detail field ends with: "This recommendation is provided by ARKA Imaging Intelligence Engine, an FDA Non-Device Clinical Decision Support tool under the 21st Century Cures Act. The ordering clinician retains full responsibility for the final decision."
- Every user-facing page includes the FDA Non-Device CDS banner.

## Code style
- TypeScript strict mode. No `any`. Every exported function has JSDoc.
- Use shadcn/ui primitives, Tailwind for styling, no custom CSS files.
- All API routes return within 800ms p95.
- Error handling: never throw from lib functions; return { data, error } tuples.

## CMS-0057-F alignment
- PA decisions must return within simulated 72h standard / 24h expedited SLA.
- Denial reasons must be specific (tied to AIIE factors), never boilerplate.
- Appeal deadline set to 180 days per the final rule.
